From 0997941766d41a3981983216600fc6405841a7b7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
Date: Thu, 11 Sep 2025 14:43:54 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] Backport: Simplify allocations and fix merge and continue
 actions [BZ #28931]

This commit backports changes from 1c37b8022e8763fedbb3f79c02e05c6acfe5a215
to glibc 2.31 to fix the following issues:

- Simplify allocations for address tuples by removing pointer chasing through PAT
- Fix merge and continue actions behavior with hosts database in getaddrinfo
- Continue action now properly discards previous results
- Merge action results in immediate lookup failure as per manual specification
- Remove unnecessary chaining of allocations across modules

Changes include:
- Modified sysdeps/posix/getaddrinfo.c to restructure allocation logic
- Added nss/tst-nss-gai-actions.c test for testing continue and merge actions
- Added test configuration files in nss/tst-nss-gai-actions.root/
- Updated nss/Makefile to include the new test

Resolves: BZ #28931
---
 nss/Makefile                               |   3 +-
 nss/tst-nss-gai-actions.c                  | 149 ++++++
 nss/tst-nss-gai-actions.root/etc/host.conf |   1 +
 nss/tst-nss-gai-actions.root/etc/hosts     | 508 +++++++++++++++++++++
 sysdeps/posix/getaddrinfo.c                | 138 ++++--
 5 files changed, 748 insertions(+), 51 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 nss/tst-nss-gai-actions.c
 create mode 100644 nss/tst-nss-gai-actions.root/etc/host.conf
 create mode 100644 nss/tst-nss-gai-actions.root/etc/hosts

