Description: CVE-2026-5928 - Fix ungetwc operating on byte stream instead of wide stream
 The _IO_wdefault_pbackfail function in libio/wgenops.c incorrectly used
 fp->_IO_read_ptr (narrow byte pointer) instead of fp->_wide_data->_IO_read_ptr
 (wide character pointer), leading to buffer under-reads and potential heap
 data disclosure. This fix corrects both pointer references to use the wide
 character data stream.
Origin: upstream, https://sourceware.org/pipermail/libc-alpha/2026-April/176798.html
Bug: https://sourceware.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=33998
Bug-Debian: https://bugs.debian.org/1134544
